Abhishek Bachchan Responds to Divorce Speculation Amid Viral Fake Video: Reports

Abhishek Bachchan has finally addressed the rumors about a split with his wife, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan. During a recent interview, he displayed his wedding ring and expressed his frustration over the speculation, while acknowledging that such rumours are part of celebrity life. Abhishek stated, 'I am still married. I don't have anything to say to you all about that. You all have blown the entire thing out of proportion, sadly. I understand why you do it; you have to file some stories. It's okay, we're celebrities, we have to take it.' The rumours started when Abhishek and Aishwarya attended separate events at the Ambani wedding, and were further fueled by Abhishekâ€™s like on a post about divorce cases.

Saif Ali Khan's Airport Outburst Draws Internet Trolls: 'Kareena Ke Kapde'

Superstar Saif Ali Khan was recently spotted at Mumbai airport, dressed stylishly in a blue kurta and matching loose pants. Despite the excitement of the paparazzi, Saif appeared visibly irritated during their interaction. A video of the encounter has gone viral, showing Saif arriving at the airport and being surrounded by photographers. When one of the paparazzi mentioned that he was standing against the light, it seemingly angered Saif. The reaction drew criticism from netizens who took to social media to express their disapproval. On the work front, Saif will next be seen in the film Devara, alongside Jr NTR and Janhvi Kapoor.

1410 views | 3 days ago

John Abraham Faces Criticism Over Photo with Manu Bhaker's Olympic Medals

Manu Bhaker returned home after making India proud at the Paris Olympics and received a grand welcome at Delhi Airport. While the country celebrated her achievements, a photo featuring actor John Abraham and Manu Bhaker sparked controversy. John met Manu upon her arrival and shared a photo on Instagram praising the Olympian, which quickly went viral. The photo, however, irked netizens, leading to a backlash as fans trolled John mercilessly for holding Manu's medals. Bhaker won bronze in both the 10m Air Pistol and the 10m Mixed Team Air Pistol events at the Olympics.
